@startuml SabaGroupBetting_MappingDictionary
!theme plain
title Match Monitor Saba Group Betting - CustID Mapping Dictionary Logic (Updated 2025-11-19)

start

:THE PROBLEM: ID Mismatch;

note left
    **Saba Platform:**
    Saba uses its own Customer ID system
    
    Example Saba CustIDs:
    - 101, 102, 103, 104, 105
    
    These are different from CTS internal IDs
end note

note right
    **CTS System:**
    CTS uses CTSCustID internally
    
    Example CTSCustIDs:
    - 5001, 5002, 5003, 5004, 5005
    
    These are CTS's internal customer identifiers
    
    **Problem:**
    Saba CustID (101) ≠ CTS CTSCustID (5001)
    
    **Impact:**
    - Association detection needs CTSCustID
    - But Saba transactions have Saba CustID
    - Need mapping to bridge the gap
end note

:THE SOLUTION: MappingCustDictionary;

note right
    **Type:** IReadOnlyDictionary<int, int>
    **Key:** Saba CustID (int)
    **Value:** CTS CTSCustID (int)
    
    **Example:**
    {
        101: 5001,
        102: 5002,
        103: 5003,
        104: 5004,
        105: 5005
    }
    
    **Purpose:**
    Bridge between Saba and CTS customer IDs
end note

partition "CREATION PROCESS" {
    :Call SP: CTS_DC_MatchMonitor_RuleGroupBettingSaba_Get;
    
    :SP Returns CTSCustomerList;
    note right
        Example CTSCustomerList:
        [
            { CustID: 101, CTSCustID: 5001 },
            { CustID: 102, CTSCustID: 5002 },
            { CustID: 103, CTSCustID: 5003 },
            { CustID: 104, CTSCustID: 5004 },
            { CustID: 105, CTSCustID: 5005 }
        ]
        
        **SQL Query in SP:**
        SELECT DISTINCT CustID, CTSCustID
        FROM MatchMonitorStagingGroupBettingSabaLive
        WHERE SequenceID <= @op_MaxSequenceID;
        
        **Tables:**
        - MatchMonitorStagingGroupBettingSabaLive
        - MatchMonitorStagingGroupBettingSabaNonLive
    end note
    
    :Extract CustID and CTSCustID;
    note right
        var customerPairs = CTSCustomerList
            .Select(x => new { 
                x.CustID,      // Saba ID
                x.CTSCustID    // CTS internal ID
            })
            .Distinct();
    end note
    
    :Create Dictionary;
    note right
        **C# Code:**
        
        MappingCustDictionary = customerPairs
            .ToDictionary(
                x => x.CustID,      // Key: Saba CustID
                x => x.CTSCustID    // Value: CTS CTSCustID
            );
        
        **Type:**
        IReadOnlyDictionary<int, int>
        
        **Read-Only:**
        Ensures dictionary is not modified during processing
    end note
    
    :Dictionary Ready;
}

partition "USAGE IN ASSOCIATION DETECTION" {
    :Get Customer Lists from Match;
    note right
        From staging data:
        - CustIDList: "101,102,103,104,105"
        - CTSCustIDList: "5001,5002,5003,5004,5005"
    end note
    
    :Create DetectAssociationParamModel;
    note right
        **C# Code:**
        
        var param = new DetectAssociationParamModel
        {
            CTSCustIds = ctsCustIDList,        // "5001,5002,5003,5004,5005"
            CustIds = custIDList,              // "101,102,103,104,105"
            IsDevice = true,
            IsAI = true,
            IsIP = true,
            Is3MatchesLast7Days = true,
            MappingCustDictionary = MappingCustDictionary  (**KEY!**)
        };
    end note
    
    :Call AssociationDetectionService;
    note right
        _assDetectService.DetectAssociation(param)
    end note
    
    partition "Inside Detection Service" {
        :Parse Customer IDs;
        
        :For each CustID, lookup CTSCustID;
        note right
            **Mapping Logic:**
            
            foreach (var custId in custIdList)
            {
                if (MappingCustDictionary.ContainsKey(custId))
                {
                    var ctsCustId = MappingCustDictionary[custId];
                    // Use ctsCustId for queries
                }
            }
            
            **Example:**
            CustID 101 -> Lookup -> CTSCustID 5001
            CustID 102 -> Lookup -> CTSCustID 5002
            etc.
        end note
        
        :Query Association Tables with CTSCustID;
        note right
            SELECT * FROM CTSAssociationGroup
            WHERE CTSCustID IN (5001, 5002, 5003, 5004, 5005)
            
            Uses mapped CTSCustID for internal queries
        end note
        
        :Return Association Results;
        note right
            Results use CTSCustID:
            [
                { CTSCustID: 5001, GroupID: 1, Type: "Device" },
                { CTSCustID: 5002, GroupID: 1, Type: "Device" },
                { CTSCustID: 5003, GroupID: 1, Type: "Device" },
                { CTSCustID: 5004, GroupID: 2, Type: "IP" },
                { CTSCustID: 5005, GroupID: 2, Type: "IP" }
            ]
        end note
    }
    
    :Map Back to Saba CustID;
    note right
        Reverse mapping for final results:
        CTSCustID -> CustID
        
        5001 -> 101
        5002 -> 102
        etc.
    end note
    
    :Return to Process Service;
}

partition "EXAMPLE SCENARIO" {
    :Example: 3 Saba customers betting together;
    
    note right
        **Match:** Liverpool vs Man City
        **Saba Customers:**
        - Saba CustID 101 (mapped to CTS 5001)
        - Saba CustID 102 (mapped to CTS 5002)
        - Saba CustID 103 (mapped to CTS 5003)
        
        **All bet:** Liverpool -0.5 @ Odds 1.95
        **Same:** DeviceID = "ABC123"
    end note
    
    :Step 1: Staging;
    note right
        INSERT INTO MatchMonitorStagingGroupBettingSabaLive
        (CustID, CTSCustID, DeviceID, ...)
        VALUES
        (101, 5001, 'ABC123', ...),
        (102, 5002, 'ABC123', ...),
        (103, 5003, 'ABC123', ...)
    end note
    
    :Step 2: Create Mapping;
    note right
        MappingCustDictionary = {
            101: 5001,
            102: 5002,
            103: 5003
        }
    end note
    
    :Step 3: Association Detection;
    note right
        Input CTSCustIDs: [5001, 5002, 5003]
        
        Query:
        SELECT * FROM CTSAssociationGroup
        WHERE CTSCustID IN (5001, 5002, 5003)
            AND DeviceID = 'ABC123'
        
        Result: All 3 customers -> GroupID = 1 (Device)
    end note
    
    :Step 4: Save Results;
    note right
        INSERT INTO MatchMonitorDetails
        (MatchID, GroupID, ListCustID, Reason, ...)
        VALUES
        (987654, 1, '101,102,103', 0, ...)
        
        **Reason = 0 (CONST_MMREASON_GROUPBETTINGSABA)**
        **Uses Saba CustIDs in final results!**
    end note
}

stop

floating note right
    ===========================================================
    MAPPING DICTIONARY SUMMARY
    ===========================================================
    
    **Why Needed:**
    - Saba uses different customer ID system
    - CTS internal queries require CTSCustID
    - Mapping bridges the gap
    
    **How Created:**
    - From SP result (CTSCustomerList)
    - Dictionary<SabaCustID, CTSCustID>
    - One-time creation per job run
    
    **Where Used:**
    - Association detection service
    - Internal CTS queries
    - Group detection logic
    
    **Benefits:**
    - Seamless integration between Saba and CTS
    - No changes to core detection logic
    - Maintainable and testable
    
    **Performance:**
    - Dictionary lookup: O(1)
    - Minimal overhead
    - Created once, used many times
    
    **Type Safety:**
    - IReadOnlyDictionary<int, int>
    - Cannot be modified after creation
    - Thread-safe for parallel processing
    
    **Tables:**
    - MatchMonitorStagingGroupBettingSabaLive
    - MatchMonitorStagingGroupBettingSabaNonLive
    - MatchMonitorDetails (Reason=0)
end note

@enduml
